    "narrative": "The Austin Waves enter today\u2019s slate with a clear focus on maximizing high-leverage spots against favorable pitching, despite some early-season volatility. **Kyle Tucker** (76.51) and **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (70.45) headline our offensive output; **Tucker** benefits significantly from wind conditions and a soft matchup against Colin Rea, while **Guerrero Jr.** leverages a strong xwOBA profile and a neutral platoon advantage to solidify his spot as a daily anchor. **Jackson Merrill** (70.76) also presents an elite start, as his high-contact profile against Zac Gallen is buoyed by a +13% boost from his dynamic platoon and a premium slot in the #3 hole. \n\nWe are navigating a few \"Lineup Pending\" situations, most notably with **Drake Baldwin** and **Dominic Smith** facing the formidable Zack Wheeler. While **Smith** managed a score of 41.10 thanks to decent BvP history, we are keeping a close eye on his placement; if he drops in the order, his utility value diminishes rapidly against an ace. The most difficult bench decision involved **Marcell Ozuna** (48.31), who sat just behind our starters in the optimizer. Ultimately, his matchup against Jacob Misiorowski lacked the situational upside provided by **Andy Pages** (60.94), whose favorable wind forecast and high-ceiling potential against Rea pushed him into the starting lineup. \n\nRisk management remains paramount today, particularly with **Gunnar Henderson** (53.01) drawing a difficult assignment against the strikeout-heavy Garrett Crochet. While **Henderson** is a must-start due to his role, the -19% SP skill penalty and platoon disadvantage make him a candidate for a lower-than-usual output. Furthermore, **Nasim Nunez** (49.10) is being started strictly for his SB potential; his bottom-of-the-order ranking acts as a drag on his efficiency, but in a 5x5 format where steals are the scarcest commodity, his legs remain a strategic necessity for the Waves.",
